Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alive, Peterman-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.72,0:04:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare they do this to our boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.99,0:04:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I never expected Duval to have such \Na handsome face under that mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.31,0:04:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, see ya! Feel free \Nto call us again anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be at your beck and call until you \Ncan safely set sail for Fishman Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.77,0:04:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Thanks, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Just quit winking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.82,0:04:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and one other thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget this, Miss Mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.23,0:04:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! My backpack!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That idiot Peterman had it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Let's go, Life is Rosy Riders!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.23,0:04:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Hand-Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.43,0:05:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Their shouts sure change a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably trying \Nto find one that clicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.03,0:05:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. Let us hurry inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.79,0:05:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to get Hachi into a bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.62,0:05:13.78,"Sign",,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,300)}"Shakky's Rip-Off Bar"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shakky! I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.05,0:05:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, welcome back, Ray-san. That \Nwas sooner than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed you guys managed to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ol' Hachi's been seriously hurt. \NWe need to get him into a bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.36,0:05:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.78,0:05:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad! I'll get a bed ready right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.55,0:05:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you said you had something \Nto tell me afterward, old guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.65,0:05:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,On the Pirate King' ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm Silvers Rayleigh, \Nthe ship's first mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,First mate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't tell them, Hatchan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.28,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We only needed his help \Nwith the coating, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You didn't realize it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know his name so well!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.17,0:06:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in so many books!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's definitely a name everyone \Nhears at least once...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold Roger...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I seem to vaguely recall a rookie named \Nthat long ago, but I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How do such a big-shot and \Nan octopus know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hachi rescued me over 20 years ago, \Nwhen I was stranded in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.90,0:06:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He saved his life. He was still \Na child at the time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hachi and I remained close after that, \Nuntil he joined the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.85,0:06:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean Arlong, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.47,0:06:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Gold Roger was \Nexecuted 22 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.86,0:06:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't get your head chopped \Noff for being first mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.99,0:07:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Navy caught the entire crew, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.32,0:07:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger turned himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The government might've made it \Nsound like they had caught him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.03,0:07:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as a way to show its power, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.63,0:07:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pirate King \Nturned himself in?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.36,0:07:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we saw an end to our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,About four years before the \Nday of his public execution,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger caught a fatal illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even Roger could avoid the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that this terminal, \Nincurable disease brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But, there was one man with the \Nskill to ease his suffering:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a man at the Twin Capes named Crocus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.69,0:08:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the most respected lighthouse \Nkeeper and doctor in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.11,0:08:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked for his help and brought him \Non as ship doctor for our final voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, three years later, \Nwhile managing to escape death,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger achieved what was \Nsaid to be impossible:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he conquered the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.75,0:08:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,C-C-Crocus-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.83,0:08:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At the Twin Capes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.79,0:08:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that brings back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.76,0:08:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! That old guy wasn't \Nthere for 50 years straight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a member of the Pirate King' crew?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.78,0:09:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, he did mention \Nbeing a ship's doctor for a few years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was a pirate for \Nthose three years, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.30,0:09:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you've met him \Nmust mean he's still doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.31,0:09:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Crocus agreed to come aboard
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because there was a certain group \Nof pirates he wanted to look for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Brook! It was you guys he set \Nout to find, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Crocus-san...! You even \Nwent to such lengths...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He was only a crewmember for three years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was unquestionably one of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.23,0:09:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At this age now, it'd be \Ngreat to see him again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.74,0:09:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happened after he conquered the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when it all began.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.97,0:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The world started calling \NRoger the "Pirate King."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.33,0:09:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He hadn't been the Pirate King \Nthe entire time before or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Titles hold no meaning \Nfor a man about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But Roger was overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.14,0:10:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved doing everything in a flashy way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it was celebrating or fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.65,0:10:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He even seemed to enjoy thinking \Nout a plan for the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,even though he wouldn't be a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, as per captain's orders, the \NRoger Pirates were secretly disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,One by one, everyone discretely left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.21,0:10:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As comrades, we all risked \Nour lives together,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.85,0:10:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know almost nothing about where \Nthey are or what they're doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.10,0:10:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, about a year after we disbanded,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger turned himself in and was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was then announced that \Nhe would be publicly executed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.64,0:11:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in Loguetown, the East \NBlue town he was born in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.19,0:11:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that many of the young \Nfaces in the town square that day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,went on to make names for themselves \Non the high seas today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.86,0:11:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The world focused its attention \Non the Pirate King' execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't attend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:12:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The final words he said went like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to die, partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.31,0:12:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The World Government and the \Nnavy must've been shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.04,0:12:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,With only one last remark from Roger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the public execution meant to serve \Nas an example to other pirates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,instead became the opening \Nceremony of the Great Pirate Age!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.16,0:12:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want it, you can have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:12:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.40,0:13:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I left everything this \Nworld has to offer there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In his last few seconds, he \Nchanged the dim flame of his life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,into a hellfire that spread across the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.99,0:13:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never laughed as much \Nas I did on that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor have I ever cried as much...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.23,0:13:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,...or drank as much as I did on that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.61,0:13:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our captain lived one hell of a life!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like we just heard something incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.21,0:14:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like a different story, \Nhearing it from someone who was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.89,0:14:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's almost as if Roger created \Nthis Great Pirate Era on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.71,0:14:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That... we still can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.81,0:14:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the people living \Nnow can create this era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.77,0:14:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain there are people who \Ninherited something from Roger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.18,0:14:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on that day in the town square.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your good friend, Shanks, \Nis probably one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.20,0:14:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You know Shanks, old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you also heard of the East \NBlue pirate known as Buggy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.02,0:14:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Buggy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.92,0:14:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of them were apprentices on our ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.08,0:14:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Shanks was on the Pirate King' ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.25,0:15:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? He didn't tell you about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.64,0:15:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran into him again on these \Nislands about 10 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd lost his trademark straw \Nhat, along with his left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.42,0:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When I asked what had happened, \Nhe cheerfully spoke about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.42,0:15:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a real shock, Rayleigh-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a kid in East Blue who said \Nthe same thing Captain Roger did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those same words of our captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.37,0:15:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've wanted to meet you-- \NMonkey D. Luffy-- ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I can't, in good mind, babble \Non about things Shanks hasn't told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:15:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, you've done \Nwell to come this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.27,0:15:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he's eagerly waiting \Nfor you in the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.26,0:16:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?! Do you think so?! I \Ncan't wait to see him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.53,0:16:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. Let's get down to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted your ship coated, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.43,0:16:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I should get back to my real work, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, coating \Ncosts a lot of money...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.65,0:16:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's all right, Hachi. I can't \Ntake money from friends of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.58,0:16:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a relief. Thank you, Rayleigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.39,0:16:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno why, but he's doing it for free!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.01,0:16:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate it! You're one generous guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.27,0:16:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like we just saved a ton of money!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.14,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rayleigh-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.41,0:16:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is the "Will of D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger's name was engraved in ancient writing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.31,0:16:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on Poneglyph I saw on a sky island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How was he able to use that writing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"I made it here. I will guide this \Ntext to the ends of the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Pirate Gol D. Roger"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.83,0:17:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you people know what happened to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.58,0:17:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,during the Void Century \Nthat began 900 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.14,0:17:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.82,0:17:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned the entirety of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.87,0:17:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Miss. You mustn't be hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.21,0:17:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue to move forward one \Nstep at a time on your own ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.77,0:17:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We-- and Ohara-- might have \Nhurried a bit too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I told you everything \Nabout history right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you still wouldn't be able to \Ndo anything as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.67,0:18:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've taken the time to see the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's possible you'll be led to \Na different answer than we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.78,0:18:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you still insist on hearing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.75,0:18:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you everything \Nabout this world right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.27,0:18:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll pass. I'll continue my journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It will all come into sight someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for what happened \Nto your homeland of Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.36,0:18:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Roger didn't decipher that writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.01,0:18:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We're pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.87,0:18:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't possibly match \Nthe intellect of geniuses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.99,0:18:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,like Clover and the scholars of Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He heard the voice of the \Nuniverse, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.79,0:19:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, are you sure, Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.66,0:19:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you didn't just \Npass up an incredible chance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm, old guy! There's one \Nmore thing I wanna ask!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.55,0:19:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The legendary great treasure, the One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.83,0:19:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.89,0:19:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna know where the treasure is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.83,0:19:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna know if the \Ntreasure exists or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.43,0:19:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We've put all our lives on \Nthe line and set out to sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,even though we don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather give up being a pirate than \Nhave the old guy tell us stuff now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.40,0:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't go on a boring adventure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,S-S-Sorry! I knew that, but it \Njust slipped out of my mouth...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't wanna know, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.22,0:19:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot! I have the "I'll Die If \NI Learn About the One Piece" disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.65,0:19:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, old guy! Don't say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.07,0:20:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.27,0:20:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Grand Line still far surpasses \Nanything you can imagine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.06,0:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your foes will be powerful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.01,0:20:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you rule this mighty sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.59,0:20:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna rule anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the freest person in this sea \Nwho's the Pirate King!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.47,0:20:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.30,0:20:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am a fan of yours, Monkey-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.66,0:20:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ship is in Grove #41, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.81,0:20:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll head over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.48,0:20:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.80,0:20:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There could be an admiral on \Nthese islands as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.59,0:20:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll only be a nuisance if we stay here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so maybe we should go shopping somewhere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.60,0:20:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this, "Laid-Back Life"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're being chased! We gotta hide, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.72,0:21:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The people chasing us might \Nshow up if we all stay together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll help him finish the work more \Nsmoothly if we lay low in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.51,0:21:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's just split up and then \Nmeet back there when he's all done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.56,0:21:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you to talk strategically about \Nmeeting up and stuff like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.95,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Shakky. Do we have any?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.03,0:21:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there's one left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.25,0:21:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a Vivre Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.40,0:21:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if you know what it is, \Nthat simplifies things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.15,0:21:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I happen to be a bit notorious myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.59,0:21:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll move it from Grove #41 to \Nsomewhere else before I start on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.44,0:21:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need three days to complete the coating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.39,0:21:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes three whole days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life depends on this work. \NIt's the fastest I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.38,0:21:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's three days of \Nwilderness survival then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.31,0:21:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How frightening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.27,0:21:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sundown in three days, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.05,0:21:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what grove I'll be on then, \Nso wherever the Vivre Cards lead you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.49,0:21:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there finishing the \Ncoating and waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.34,0:22:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You should probably also \Nbuy whatever you'll need
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.98,0:22:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for your underwater voyage \Nto Fishman Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.76,0:22:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Luffy-chin! Everyone! Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.75,0:22:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Thanks so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I caused you so much trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.65,0:22:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't thank you guys enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.64,0:22:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show you the way to Fishman \NIsland, so don't worry about a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.94,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out for the Navy \Nfor the next three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.43,0:22:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hachi! Get plenty of bed rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.81,0:22:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's meet again in three \Ndays. We'll see you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.58,0:22:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're up against an admiral! We gotta \Nmake sure none of us gets killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.62,0:22:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say unlucky things like that!
